        <heading>1336.  Judicial regulation of mode of partition</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1336.  Judicial regulation of mode of partition.
The judge who decides on a suit for a partition and on the mode of effecting it, has a right to regulate this mode as may appear to him most convenient and most advantageous for the general interest of the co-heirs, in conformity, nevertheless, with the following provisions.</p>
        </content>
